future readme




On Windows PowerShell, run:

py -3 tools\dump_cli_parser.py --format json > aerolitctl-cli-surface.json
py -3 tools\dump_cli_parser.py --format text > aerolitctl-cli-surface.txt

On Linux/RHEL, run:

python3 tools\dump_cli_parser.py --format json > aerolitctl-cli-surface.json
python3 tools\dump_cli_parser.py --format text > aerolitctl-cli-surface.txt





On Windows PowerShell, run:

py -3 tools\scan_argparse_static.py --root . --format text --output aerolitctl-static-argparse-scan.txt
py -3 tools\scan_argparse_static.py --root . --format json --output aerolitctl-static-argparse-scan.json

On Linux/RHEL, run:

python3 tools/scan_argparse_static.py --root . --format text --output aerolitctl-static-argparse-scan.txt
python3 tools/scan_argparse_static.py --root . --format json --output aerolitctl-static-argparse-scan.json

The output files should be portable either way. You can run it on Windows, then upload the generated .txt and .json files here.




Run it on Windows:

py -3 tools\check_completion.py --root .

Or use your generated parser dump:

py -3 tools\check_completion.py --root . --surface-json aerolitctl-cli-surface.json

Run it on Linux/RHEL:

python3 tools/check_completion.py --root .

Or:

python3 tools/check_completion.py --root . --surface-json aerolitctl-cli-surface.json





